This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it deals with the construction of adversarial examples for deep networks and the analysis of their activation patterns. It may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories, as these fields are closely related to machine learning. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category, as adversarial examples can be used to attack security systems based on deep learning.
